  "text": "In the light of lemma 1, going from a symbolic alphabet to a proper one can be viewed as a step towards determinising the automaton with respect to its timed language. From here one can simply use classical automata theoretic techniques to determinise the automaton w.r.t. its symbolic language. (Of course, since we deal with infinite words we will need to go from a Büchi to a Muller or Rabin acceptance condition [CITATION_1] ). Theorem 1. The class of IDA's over (Σ, Op) are effectively closed under the boolean operations of union, intersection, and complement.",
